Archer and ServiceNow are effective because they use a normalized relational model. 
This database is created to mirror that philosophy and have a single repository of ultimate truth.

The goal is to separate:

- Assets
- Technical Evidence
- Compliance Controls
- Framework Mappings
- Vulnerabilities
- Risks
- POA&M
- Scan History

This avoids duplication. A single piece of evidence (e.g., "BitLocker Enabled") can satisfy multiple frameworks without being stored multiple times.

